<a name="newsitem967752340,89076,"></a><font color="#ff0000"><table height="22" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" background="/images/dateback.jpg"><tr>	<td height="22"><img src="/images/dateleft.jpg" border=0 alt=""></td>	<td width=450 height="22"><SPAN Class="newsdate">Thursday, August 31, 2000</SPAN></td>	<td height="22"><img src="/images/dateright.jpg" border=0 alt=""></td></tr></table><br><br></font> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Gordon Infobits: Afternoon Edition</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 1:05 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Gordon got an early start on the Gameplay Board today with the following posts he generated:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009890.html"><b>Shadow Knights Dead?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: When asked what spells are useful to a group a SK can cast the response has Been NONE or one<br>Darkness??? maybe<br><br>On a poll at: <br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/</a><br>SK&#8217;s are DEAD last!!!!]</i></font> <br><br>EverQuest has 14 classes. *Someone* had to be last. Being last here is not really indicative of any problem. Besides, the difference between SKs and some of the other bottom classes is really not that great. For instance, someone could say "SKs are preferred over monks in groups 47% of the time", and suddenly it wouldn't sound as bad. <br><br>But that poll did not ask who you want in your group, it asked what is the *FIRST* class you look for when forming a group. There's a tremendous difference between those two questions. Of course regardless of what question you ask that has people rank a list, there will still always be someone in the list who is last. <br><br>I think that SKs need to start doing what I sugggested rogues do a few months ago: Show people what you can do, educate them in the ways of an sk, but most importantly, be cool with people. Your personality and reputation has far more to do with what groups you get into than your class. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009933.html"><b>Mez Stacking</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Mez stacking is broken. Every other spell line works this way. Better spells overwrite the weaker ones.]</i></font> <br><br>I'm sorry that you don't agree, but as I said before, mez spell stacking works as intended. NPCs only know if they are mez'd or not, and the spell effect is absolute regardless of the duration of the spell. I've spread the word around that this is indeed not a bug, so you shouldn't get conflicting information going forward.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009938.html"><b>Velicous Creatures</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: PLEASE tell me its not a rehash of exsisting MOBS / Monsters with pretty new colors.]</i></font> <br><br>There will of course be some new variaties of existing creatures, as there is in Kunark, but there will also be a bunch of new ones as well. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: P.S. Will this new graphics engine revamp ALL of Everquest or just the new areas in SoV]</i></font> <br><br>As with Kunark, the new areas will adopt newer and more advanced technology. "EverQuest Proper", however, has to remain as it was in the original release.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009940.html"><b>Dragons</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Why are we told that the three dragons for the high level are now rare spawns? Why are we facing more hardship the higher the lvls we get? I really think that this change is rediculous and should have been annouced before you waisted alot of people time.]</i></font> <br><br>I'm afraid that I don't understand your complaint. NPC spawn rates/times etc., are never broadcast to the players. Secondly, I'm not sure what you mean by "waisted a lot of people's time". If you mean that people were waiting in the zone when the servers came up to get the dragons, and they weren't there, that doesn't really equate to much lost time at all. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009953.html"><b>Mana Battery</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Gordon, about this quote:<br><br>"I'm sorry, but we've ruled out creating "mana batteries". The greatest extent that we can implement a mana battery is done with..." <br><br>Why, then, do you continue to leave bards broken, serving nothing more than this purpose? Its what we've been complaining about for ages.]</i></font> <br><br>I don't understand what you are getting at here, if you could elaborate. The subject of allowing enchanters to create mana batteries, and the existing modulation rod and the necromancer "conversion" line are not, in my opinion, related to bards. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009963.html"><b>What would you do if you caught someone cheating?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: The GM could not verify that this item was in the players posession and gave that player the benefit of doubt and reimbursed the item. I was immediately told this occurance by the player. They bragged how they got over on the gm.]</i></font> <br><br>We'd certainly appreciate you /reporting such things if witnessed. Our new customer service policies regarding reimbursement is based on our ability to determine things from the logs, but you are correct that we will give the benefit of the doubt lacking any concrete evidence to the contrary. <br><br>However, if this is abused everyone is aware of the impact upon the game it will have, which is why we ban any scammers immediately.</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
<a name="newsitem967751594,26913,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Yakatizma Infobits (Trade Skills)</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 12:53 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Yakatizma hit the new <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=Coalition+of+Tradesfolk&number=8">Coalition of Tradesfolk Board</a> recently and has made several posts to date:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000076.html"><b>Recipes</b></a><br>The recipes themselves are indeed the simplest part of the process. It is the many factors that play into balance and any extra coding that needs to be done that is the most time consuming. Once the properties, economic values, availability and difficulty of the product and its components plus the impact of the final product on existing items are determined the recipe table can be produced and placed for testing. This is why some content with very low balancing issues can be implemented quickly and others, blacksmithing for example, with high balance issues are very time consuming. For instance, the silk thread, bandages, small bag, and silk cord, all of which had extremely minimal balance issues were placed on test server the same day I saw them on the wishlist, but of course for them to appear on the live servers they must go through testing and wait for an available patch.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000066.html"><b>Chemistry</b></a><br>There is one other class that dabbles in a chemistry of sorts that can mix dyes besides Shaman.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000047.html"><b>Trade Skill Messages</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Implement a new message for tradeskills with the same display range as /say.<br>For example, if successful: "A sparkle of light gleams from Laestir's jewelry kit."<br>Alternately, if unsuccessful: "Laestir empties his jewelry kit of ruined materials."]</i></font><br><br>This is a very desirable feature in my opinion. I will attempt to have it addressed at the next tuning meeting.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000036.html"><b>Fletching</b></a><br>I'll come up with an arrow recipe that uses ****atrice beaks but the benefit of the arrow will have to be in its damage/delay ratio and its magic/non magic flag. Unfortunately the current engine does not allow for missiles to have procs. Another problem would be the fact that items with spell effects can not be made stackable, making storage and reloading of missiles with effects difficult.<br>--<br>If there are other items that you feel would make sense as fletching components in addition to the c-ockatrice beak I would like to see a list of them posted.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000014.html"><b>Tailoring</b></a><br>Thank you for the feedback. I have changed the icon for silk threads to the "urticating hairs" graphic, changed the weight of Silk Bandages to 0.2 and removed the skill check from creating Silk Thread.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000105.html"><b>Enchanters</b></a><br>Fear not enchanters. The summon mana series of spells has been expanded for use in enchanted trade skill items and you may find that enchanted precious metals have uses outside of jewelry craft. It is true that some items with special properties may need a cleric or shaman in addition to an enchanter, and in the case of some cultural items from societies without casters may exclude the enchanter entirely. However, the magic items produced with the assistance of a Cleric or Shaman are very noticeably different than those produced with solely enchanters. Enchanters will remain true to their namesake as masters of enchantments.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum8/HTML/000013.html"><b>Tinkering</b></a><br>For tinkering to produce the mechanical wonders and blunders that gnomes are famous for it must be fairly heavily reliant on products of other trade skills as well as odds and ends found by the gnome as he adventures. The plus side of the dependency on other trade skills and treasure drops is that the difficulty to create a tinkered item will allow for more beneficial and/or powerful end products. Once the blacksmithing goes live I will be continuing to add content to the trade skills, including tinkering as I work on Velious. If any of you tinkers have good ideas that you would like to see implemented for the trade skill please post them on this board, ideally with the prefix Wish :(  title of post)there were some good suggestions for several trade skills on the wishlist board and now that this board is back up hopefully there will be many more.</UL>On a sidenote, you may have noticed I have started putting two spaces inbetween posts on the infobits.  If you like it double-spaced or single-spaced please leave a comment indicating it.
</SPAN><P><br>
