<a name="newsitem967727597,20815,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Gordon Infobits: Morning Edition</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 6:13 AM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Gordon made a few more posts late last night on the Gameplay Board:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009744.html"><b>Positive GM Experience</b></a><br>Thanks for posting! :)<br><br>As a note, we are currently working on implementing a version of the GMRes that isn't subject to the time restriction and doesn't apply resurrection effects.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009575.html"><b>CS Help Needed</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Our records indicate that your Station Member account was cancelled at your request.  If you would like to re-activate your account, please contact Customer Service at 1-888-STATION or at accounts@station.sony.com.]</i></font> <br><br>Hmmm, when you try to enter the game it should prompt you to subscribe. You might try going into the "Accounts" screen and seeing if anything is prompted there. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: So I call the number, I get hung up on, busy signals and then the guy on the phone tells me that I should be able to log in and take care of everything and reset up the billing.]</i></font> <br><br>I'm sorry that you had a problem with the phone system. We've hired a number of new tech-support and customer-service representatives, it's likely that one of them had a problem with the phone system. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: So I try that -- Am I surprised when I get the same message trying to log in? NO! But guess what? I have to CALL BACK. Yes, another test of paitence. So I figure lets email, its easier and easier to get a response. Well, amazed. Its been almost a week and a half still no solid answer on whats wrong with my account.]</i></font> <br><br>I'll forward your post to the customer-service management team. I do indeed apologize for the problems.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009674.html"><b>Colors, Colors Everywhere</b></a><br>Per today's patch, the client will write the original colors as defaults when creating the file. People can delete the file to have one with the old defaults written. Of course they still might need some help deleting the file, but that's much easier than editing the file for those less literate.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009682.html"><b>GM Abuse or Bug?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: I noticed while enchanting silver bars, that if you interrupt the cast you lose the bar. I chalked it up as a bug at first.. until I started to think about it. After some time to analyze the situation I determined that it must be a feature. It makes sense that if you screw up tyring to do something as magic intense as enchanting metals.. you should lose the metal.]</i></font> <br><br>Indeed it is not a bug. All spells use the component in the event of interruption. This was actually a surprise to me when I first came to work here as I'd never noticed it with my character. As it turns out, it's been this way since release. <br><br>I do identify with the original poster, as that is an expensive component to lose, however the GM was correct in that it was not a bug.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009741.html"><b>"Auto Meditate Works =)"</b></a><br>Hehe :) It's funny when the neurons get wired to complete an action; It's hard to reroute them. I have a couple of problems like that myself, and sometimes unintentionally type the wrong word when responding to posts. A week or two ago I was responding to a post about spell "duration", and somehow typed "donation" :)</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
