<a name="newsitem967687711,86962,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">GM Event on Povar</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 7:08 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
The following report was sent in by Ganzon:<BLOCKQUOTE>This occured at 8/29/00, around 2AM EST. <br><br>-GM Event on Povar-<br><br>While hunting Sand Giants in Oasis, I came across two <br>named Sand Giants standing near the orc highway. They didn't attack onsight, <br>and just stood there for a few minutes. Reports that other named Sand Giants <br>appeared at the docks were confirmed, and after a moment Harziz Garnt, a <br>midget Sand Giant (about the size of a human) began to kill at the docks. <br><br>He had  a partner who was about the size of a gnome casting wizard spells. <br>Reports of his brethren on a killing spree at the Orc Highway were also <br>confirmed, and that was when we got smart and decided to retreat to the first <br>pillar at the water to regroup. The Giants were killing off everyone, <br>disregarding race and religion...they had to be stopped. We formed assault <br>groups and hunted down Harziz Garnt, who, when attacked, called for his <br>gnome-sized friend to cast a devestating area of effect-rain spell in the <br>dead center of our mass of about 30 people. My party dove out of the assault <br>group in time to avoid being hit by the second and third rains, but most were <br>not that lucky. <br><br>We regrouped again at the first pillar and buffed up while <br>the Giants were enjoying themselves by killing weaker people. After everyone <br>was at full mana and full health, we went after Harziz again who had taken <br>the gypsies hostage with his gnome-sized friend. We pulled him away from the <br>gypsies and proceeded to beat him down, Fearing his friend so that we <br>wouldn't be hit with anymore devestating area spells. After a few minutes of <br>nuking and melee, we got him on the run, and eventually killed him. We had <br>very little time to celebrate because the other assault group was being <br>wrecked by the gnome Giant. He went down fairly easy though, once we got <br>enough melee people in there to interrupt his castings. The third giant to <br>die was one of the large ones, Nirziz Pire, who ran faster than a Shaman with <br>Spirit of Cheetah. <br><br>I myself didn't get to see the fourth one go down, or even <br>if he did, but I remember hearing his shout about how we "won the sands this <br>day." <br><br>/OOC As far as I know no one was able to loot anything, and none of the <br>Giants were part of a GM quest. This was all a big fun thing, and no one lost <br>exp for dying at the hands of the Giants.  <br><br>Ganzon Actueras,<br>35th Shaman of The Sentinals.</BLOCKQUOTE>Thank you.
</SPAN><P><br>
