<a name="newsitem967687452,59905,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Gordon Infobits: The Revenge</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 7:04 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Gordon Wrinn, aka Abashi (aka Top Secret Goverment Message Board Posting Machine), let loose another round of board posts on the Gameplay Board.  Here's the scoop: <UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009659.html"><b>Thicken Mana Line</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Why not make the mana vials expendable items that recover a certain amount of mana when consumed? The higher up the mana vial spell is, the more mana is regained by drinking the vial. You can keep down the abuse of this item by making it so they cannot be placed in any containers. That and the high level ones will be VERY expensive to make (4 rubies for the highest level mana vial).]</i></font> <br><br>I'm sorry, but we've ruled out creating "mana batteries". The greatest extent that we can implement a mana battery is done with the modulation rod (which eats hitpoints and is lore) and with your friendly neighborhood necromancer.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009672.html"><b>Smokers Getting Damaged While Taking Breaks</b></a><br>You could just turn your autoattack function on and back up against a zone wall. Anything coming after you would then most likely be in front of you, be auto-targeted, and attacked when it approached. The best suggestion I can offer is of course that you camp to take your breaks. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009656.html"><b>Disillusioned Enchanters</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Why are enchanters not given the ability to cast these very same race/creature illusions upon either the group as a whole, or individuals in a group? (You already HAVE the code for specific-case faction issues with the already in- game illusion series of spells)]</i></font> <br><br>I agree that the code exists, is in game, and would be easy to do. Our reasons for not implementing illusions on others via enchanters is that its not what we had in mind for them. It's part of the premise for the enchanter class. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Are you explicitly saying that in order for an enchanter to cast any illusion spell on themselves/others that a faction adjustment MUST take place and that for this reason, Verant would not attempt to try to code a spell allowing an illusion change to any NPC model in a particular zone? Or would Verant consider allowing enchanters to create illusions with no faction adjustments?]</i></font> <br><br>Illusions always have faction adjustments. They adjust the "race" portion of the faction formula. The game/faction engine does not allow someone to appear as a different race without adopting the faction settings for that race. As such, special allowances have been made for every race that can be illusioned. Opening more races to this would require a massive revamp of the faction engine and how it interacts with illusions. That revamp would constitute a major change to what defines EverQuest. Furthermore, the diversity the various areas in the game would surely lead to some bugs that would be implemented in the course of the revamp. Given these reasons, a change along these lines does not have benefits that outweigh cost. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Aside from faction issues, are you saying that by essentially allowing the 'minor illusion' spell to also include NPC models, in addition to the myriad of other object models in a particular zone, that this creates some sort of a problem? If so, could you please elaborate?]</i></font> <br><br>I think that I covered this one above. If I need to elaborate further, please let me know. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009655.html"><b>Harmony Upgrade</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Level 24 would be perfect for a harmony upgrade that could be castable indoors. I think this would greatly increase numbers in mid level dungeons, were crowed control is needed most.]</i></font> <br><br>Harmony is too powerful to extend to the indoors. We'd have to make it resistable and give a chance for the whole group of targets to come running in order to balance it.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009648.html"><b>More Hybrid Issues</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Abashi you said that hybrids spells are largely useless in a well balanced group <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009260.html">http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009260.html</a>  ]</i></font><br><br>I just reread my post to that thread, and I believe that I indicated that the spells aren't useless even when in a group where the parnet class is present. I certainly didn't say that "hybrids spells are largely useless in a well-balanced group".<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009647.html"><b>Rowl's Day Off: Bug Found!</b></a><br>Oops :)<br><br>Rowyl's off for a couple of days but I'll mention it to him when he gets back. I'd agree that that is pretty useless until we get the change made. Unless if course if you want to type the emote out every time. Sorry about that.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009638.html"><b>Control Item Farming</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: I will use the FBSS(flowing black silk sash) for my example. Consider if that only ONE FBSS can be looted by each player on a server. Each account allows 8 players per server. That means you could only loot 8 FBSS's per account, then you would have to purchase any others you might want(for whatever reason) from other players.]</i></font> <br><br>This is much like the "Lore for Life" suggestion that was posed here several months ago, suggesting that once an item was in a characters possession, that they could not get another one, whether it be via drop, or trade, or possibly a combination of one or another. It's an idea that I like, however not something that's compatible with EverQuest's core mechanics. It might however be applicable to future products.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009643.html"><b>Can you riposte a riposte? </b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: This can be fun in an arena environment between two melee classes who use their 100% riposite chance disciplines at the same time.]</i></font> <br><br>Yeah, I was so worried about that little feature when it first came out I grabbed a tester and had it tested right there for fear it would crash the server :)<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009635.html"><b>Velious Questions </b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Velious Questions <br><br>Your questions really aren't related to Velious, but are more along the lines of general gameplay questions.]</i></font> <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 1) Will playes every be able to pick the handiness of their character? i.e. Left handed players<br>2) Will anything be done to make Ogres look less goofy? A way to turn<br>the butt scraching off would help, I think the best way would be a long grey beard, but somthing needs to be done ]</i></font><br><br>We have no plans along these lines at present. Character geometry, animations, and the combat system are considered complete and as such are unlikely to change going forward. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 3) Will players be able to customize thier clothing? i.e. Dyes, or maybe an option for what clothing will show up and what doesn't, like<br>the goofy looking bronze helm for Ogres ]</i></font><br><br>To a certain extent, something along one of the lines you've suggested is planned for the future. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 4) not related to Velious, but Next time there is an expantion that includes a new race, PLEASE take a poll on what new race you guys will make. Everyone I've talked to likes this Idea. ]</i></font><br><br>It is very unlikely that new player races will be forthcoming in EverQuest.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009634.html"><b>Overlapping Mezes?</b></a><br>The stacking of mez spells works as intended. They are not designed so that more powerful mez's overwrite weaker ones.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009628.html"><b>The Rathe In Distress</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post:From a player's perspective, a multiple Hate or Fear zone system would be just fantastic. A player would just select PlaneFearA or PlaneFearB and so forth when trying to zone in. This would not ruin the economy as the items are already no drop nor would it throw the armor rate off balance as it already has been off balance negatively for months. Bottom line - no matter how you implement it, either the plane armor drop rate has to increase - or the number of places where you can get it has to increase. Either duplicate Fear and Hate, implement new planes or increase drop rate.]</i></font> <br><br>We've addressed the "multiple copy" proposals before. In short, this is not something that we would implement. It would indeed mess up the economy, create unmanagable server load, and be inconsistant with our ideals for the world. There are more than enough areas in the game to support everyone who wishes to adventure at every level, and we're about to add an entire new continent. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post:The guilds on the Rathe server favor a reservation system]</i></font> <br><br>That aside, I have to put my "reservation system disclaimer" in now. We do not support nor endorse, nor will we enforce any type of "reservation system" in use on the servers for the purpose of scheduling dragons, planes, other zones, or other encounters. Compliance with them is entirely voluntary on the part of the groups involved.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008951-5.html"><b>Saviente Fired?</b></a><br>I aplogize for the insensitive smiley on the end of Chris's post. He signs all of his posts in that matter and I've asked him to be a little more careful with it in the future. <br><br>To elaborate, privacy laws and professional policy prohibit us from discussing the issue in the detail that is being requested in this thread. It's not a matter of "corporate doublespeak" as a few have suggested in this thread, its that we cannot expose ourselves to discussing someone's personal life in public without their consent. <br><br>I appreciate all of the support that has been shown in the thread, as it's always nice to hear when our customer service representatives liked by our customers, but that is the extent to which I can address the issue. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009625.html"><b>Was Strength of Earth Modified?</b></a><br>No spells were modified as a result of this patch. And no, the changes to the "Sense" series really don't qualify as spell changes (meaning a change to the spell database). <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009619.html"><b>"Are you ever going to fix Archery?"</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Yea, like this will ever get a response.]</i></font> <br><br>If you'd like to repost this, sans insults, you'd have a better chance. I was reading your post, and getting a reply ready when I reach the insulting section of the original post followed by this one, and decided against responding. Normally I don't even comment to this extent on such a thread, but I thought I'd pop in and let you know why posts of this nature are unlikely to "ever get a response". <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009179.html"><b>Suggestions to Improve EQ</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 1. GM Events-<br><br>I posted a snip about this on the topic of the week thread, but thought I would bring it up here. Just to remind you to look back there]</i></font> <br><br>The discussion of the week thread deals with broad issues from more of a philosophical standpoint rather than individual ideas. There's about 450 responses to those threads, which I of course won't comment on them all. If you had some specific ideas you might want to post them outside of the thread. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 2. Gods-<br><br>I think Gods should be increased in difficulty. An absurd request eh? Lemme explain. These are the Gods, plain and simple they should be the hardest in the game. But of course the reward would be the "best" in the game I know it sounds odd, but hey it's just a suggestion. ]</i></font><br><br>We do indeed have plans to do this in the near future. The current loot from the deities will be moved to other encounters of a similar current difficulty, and the deities themselves will get much tougher and gain new loot. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Someone kills Karana, It doesn't rain for a month in game. Something along those lines. I see Gods as big and all mighty. If you kill one of em stuff is gonna go down! Once again, just a suggestion. ]</i></font><br><br>Ahhh, I see where you are going now, you just want it to stop raining in the Karanas :) :)<br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 3. Trade Skills<br><br>I think everyone can agree these need to be redone big time. ]</i></font><br><br>In progress. Check out the tradeskill board. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 4. Towns-<br><br>Now all these revamping to dungeons, but I was thinking, what about revamping a town or 2? I think this would be great! Everquest is an always expanding game right? A new look on an old town would be awesome. ]</i></font><br><br>While we can make changes to NPCs in town, and the things they do, we're restricted from making world-geometry or texture changes due to download size in most cases. We'll certainly keep the ideas in mind though. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 5. Random Spawns in Outdoor areas<br><br>This is always fun. I love being in a huge zone and someone saying "Who is Joe Blow?!" And everyone says I dunno never heard of em. "What's the loc?" I really like the sense that you don't know if you're gonna find some really kewl monster just running around in the middle of no where.]</i></font> <br><br>I agree that this is fun. Of course there can be too much of a good thing. These encounters remain special since they are rare in nature. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 6. Meditate book<br><br>Now this probably has been suggested before, but I'll give it a shot. How about when someone sits down to meditate, it shows them looking at a book. I mean, the book graphic is there right?]</i></font> <br><br>Cool idea! :)</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
