<a name="newsitem967679933,9942,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Gordon Infobits</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 4:58 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Big day on the boards so far for Verant's Gordon Wrinn.  Here's what he's posted today so far on the Gameplay Board:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009258.html"><b>Enchanter Questions</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Will Enchanters ever get the ability to Illusion others? I know this MAY raise some faction issues, but then again so do the Druids wolf illusions. Anyhow, At higher levels, Illusion other: (insertrace here) would make up for the lack of illuions ant the higher levels. After all Enchanters are the "Master of Illusions" heck, we even get called illusionists at high levels. Please let me know what u think of this idea. I am rather curious]</i></font> <br><br>There have been several posts as of late concerning other illusions. One limitation is that certain models are only available in certain zones, where other models are available globally. Illusions are for the most part restricted to zones in which the model exists. It has been suggested that we should allow enchanters to illusion to the "nearest animate entity" in the zone, however that would indeed present faction issues. <br><br>Each illusion requires specific case-coding to handle the faction issues associated with each illusion. The number of different NPC body-types in the game would make that difficult, and in many cases impossible.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009254.html"><b>/guildmessage Suggestion</b></a><br>Hey there, just dropping a note to let you know that we've seen this request *many* times here on the boards. It's something that we may be able to do at some point, but we really can't promise it as a coming feature.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009260.html"><b>Rangers</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: 4. Spells givenn to Rangers are useless in groups and outside of groups do not allow Soloing exp giving mobs.]</i></font> <br><br>Out of your four points, I'd agree with all but #4. The spells aren't useless, and are only eclipsed when fighting in a group where there is a druid. Even then, the rangers mana can be used to do things like buff pets and help out between fights, so they aren't total invalidated. <br><br>Also, as I've mentioned before, the soloability argument isn't indicative of any problem, as the class is not designed to solo. Finally, your other three points simply state the design, and are also not indicative of any problems. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Archery is a Joke.]</i></font> <br><br>I disagree, especially after the double-damage upgrade above level 50. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: And yes we do less damage Dual Yielding than Warriors.]</i></font> <br><br>There are many weapons out there that can be used by both warriors and rangers. Ranger damage output is within a percentage point or two of a warrior wielding a weapon of the same quality. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Do a who all Ranger 50-60 on Cazic thule with 2800 people on line and you will see 20-25 and who all Ranger 40 50 you see 20 more any day of the week. This should be telling you something.]</i></font> <br><br>Actually, people didn't start complaining about drops in ranger numbers until the "rangers suck" drive started shortly after Kunark was released. It is, in my opinion, the same thing that happened in regards to rogues complaining on the boards about how bad they were. I think that the community is starting to realize how valuable rogues are at this point, so the numbers will start rising again. <br><br>Rangers might have a bit more of a difficult time ahead of them, as recovering from a "we suck" drive is very difficult. Remember that when a bunch of people get on the board and complain about how bad they feel their class is, other people read those posts and begin to believe that it's true. It's a bit of a self-fulfilling prophecy.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009267-2.html"><b>Ralls and PvP Issues</b></a><br>The GM probably shouldn't have stated it in such absolute terms, but no, there are no plans to implement a move at present. That however does not equate to "There will be no move". <br><br>The quotes posted by Nanuvis-RZ on the first page of this thread still apply. And I do apologize, but this is not an issue that I'll be able to give periodic updates on, as we've been shifting priorities a bit here. <br><br>The PvP servers are still primarily PvE, like all of the other servers. PvP is there as an addition to the environment. As such, if we have to decide between changes that will improve things across all servers, or only on the PvP servers, we'll have to go with the one across all servers first. <br><br>My recommendation would be that if you absolutly cannot stand playing on Rallos any longer, you should create a character on one of the other servers and play there. As long as the population on Rallos continues to be strong, we're not going to assign priority to drastically changing the server environment. I'm not trying to be short or gruff, but we are going to need some type of sign that drastic changes are indeed wanted on that server beyond what's on these boards to provide us with a business reason to assign it some priority.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009261.html"><b>Crashing Bug</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Anyone else having problems with the game crashing to their desktop from the character select screen? the first time it happened was when i tried zoning into WC,then i crashed,then i tried to enter norrath then it crashed again. Anyone else having this problem ?]</i></font> <br><br>There was a crash bug fixed in this patch that would cause people who had exited the game to crash upon trying to come back in, but that bug shouldn't have caused you to crash out of the game itself. We also included a bunch of code-optimizations in today's patch, so that might help out with some of the random crashes we've heard of.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009280.html"><b>Blacksmithing Question</b></a><br>I have a note in to the designer responsible for tradeskills to find out if this is an oversight or by design. I hope to have word back later today or tomorrow. You might also consider posting about this on the tradeskills board, which that designer will visit regularly.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009284.html"><b>Way to Stop Camping</b></a><br>This was suggested before under the moniker "Lore for Life". It's a nice idea that I like as a feature, but unfortunately not likely to be compatible with EQ at any point. It's one of those things that needs to be designed as a core foundation of the game in the begining.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009304.html"><b>EQ Slang Not Understood By All</b></a><br>I apologize for that. I usually try to define any abbreviation that I use at least once within my response if it isn't already defined by the poster. Sometimes I forget a couple :)<br><br>I have the same problem with some of the posts I read. I've had to go asking around the office just to see if someone knows that a particular abbreviation is. <br><br>By the way, what is a BMT?<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009311.html"><b>No Drop = Soulbound?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: I guess this isn't really a question, but rather a suggestion. Could you just make it so that a no drop item is soulbound in the way that Sebilis/Charisis/VP keys are?]</i></font> <br><br>We "soulbound" the keys so you wouldn't have to do the quest to get the key twice just for the purpose of going back and getting your body. Making all nodrop items soulbound is another matter entirely, and not related to the initial change. We did this as a matter of courtesy and to help players out. There was no balance issue or gameplay design that necessitated completing the key-quest twice. <br><br>Though we certainly won't make all nodrop items soulbound, we do indeed now have a way to add additional value items that are awarded. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009253.html"><b>Why do Hybrids have an EXP penalty?</b></a><br>This subject is fairly well covered in the FAQ at http:/everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009558.html"><b>Venril Sathir Faction</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Just want to know if there will ever be a valid story line in the game to explain why I can't group with my friends in the dungeons in kunark which hit venril sathir faction.]</i></font> <br><br>I believe that the zones have been in long enough now that someone can reasonably extrapolate the story line involved. I'll give a hint to enable you to do some further research: <br><br>Who runs Karnor's, Charasis, and Kaesora?<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009249.html"><b>Leveling</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Gordon, if you wish to respond to this, respond with 'Actually Azrael178, there are tons of stuff that have yet to be figured out, even at your level.' I mean, only say that if it is true, but give me some clue as to how close I was when I said most everthing in game (save Planar/Veeshans Peak) has been solved.]</i></font> <br><br>Actually Azrael178, "Actually" is one of my favorite words (next to "evidently") :)<br><br>Seriously though, thanks for the post and I understand where you are coming from. It would be fair to say that most things in game have been solved by one person or another, which is why we keep putting new things in. It's certainly difficult if not impossible to put content in at a rate higher than it can be consumed. For instance, it takes an author months to write a book, while it takes only a few hours to read one. The guys here, for instance, have been working for weeks on putting together some really special quests for all of the classes. I think that it will only be a couple of weeks before they have all been solved by someone. <br><br>I think that the important thing here is that though things might have been solved by someone, they haven't been solved by you, yet. There is still tons of content out there for you to explore, and we put more in nearly every week. I think that we can entertain you for sometime to come :)<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009595.html"><b>Adding Target's Name to Socials</b></a><br>We do indeed plan on adding the "@" to the chat channels as well as emotes in the near future. I've also asked Rowyl to include additional identifiers for gender-specific subjective (he, she, it), objective (him, her, it), and possesive (his, her, its) pronouns.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009244.html"><b>The Unknown Pet Command</b></a><br>In beta, "/pet attack" would not automatically assume the target, so you had to enter the name, or get hit first to initiate the attack. At that time I created a macro of "/pet attack a". That handled most encounters fairly well :)<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009617.html"><b>Have NPC Pets Die With Master</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Makes sense. Happens to PCs. Why not NPCs too?]</i></font> <br><br>See the FAQ. NPCs can do things that PCs cannot.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009236.html"><b>More on Discussion of the Week</b></a><br>When the first thread was closed due to size, I started another at: <br><br><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009074.html">http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009074.html</a><br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009624.html"><b>Idea Suggestion</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post:We have wizards, that get some natural immunity to resistences. And we have spells that lower resist, and items that raise resist. So why no items that give you a bonus to cut through a mobs resist? Like most resist items, they are in of themselves not always the best item to wear durning normal day to day play. But there are times when you put them on for special occasions. An example would be fire resist items for a Naggy raid.]</i></font> <br><br>I'm not sure I understand the question. <br><br>There are spells in the game that lower the resists of the target. There are items in game that increase your resists. There are items in game that proc spells that reduce the resistances of the target, and wizards innately roll versus lower resist-scores by the target once above level 35. <br><br>Are you asking for an item that YOU wear, that decreases the ability of the target to resist? If so, we do not have the ability to flag specific items with the ability to reduce the resist rate of a target without going through a spell effect. Furthermore, there are sufficient methods available to reduce resist scores on a target, so the suggested change really isn't something that is needed in game, and as such would be low priority if we ever did decide to move in this direction.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008466.html"><b>Sound Fix</b></a><br>To my knowledge, all known sound-related crash bugs were fixed a while ago. We are indeed working on a new sound engine to improve the way sounds are handled in EverQuest and improve the use of EAX though. <br><br>I do keep hearing enough anecdotal evidence concerning sound-related crashes to indicate that they still might be happening. What kind of card are you using? I have an SBLive in both my work and home PCs, and never crash with them. People having crashes usually say that they have an SBLive as well. If so, do you have all of the latest drivers? <br><br>Finally, if you disable your sound card in the device manager, do the crashes go away. Obviously I'm not suggesting that this is a "fix" for any sound related issue, but it is the final test to determine whether a crashing problem is sound-related.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009021-2.html"><b>The /Petition System</b></a><br>I've personally petitioned many times while in my player character to report names or profanity, however I've never petitioned for some issue requiring "help" within game. <br><br>This fairly well represents the average player in game. There are on the other hand players who petition quite frequently for help of one kind or another. Sometimes it's due to a run of bad luck or perhaps system-related issues. <br><br>At some point, I'd like to see us start tracking petitions made within the last month or so and using that data to establish priorities for helping the customers. Chances are that if someone hasn't petitioned in the last month, and he or she is petitioning now, they need help right away.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008941.html"><b>GMs as NPCs?</b></a><br>Uluhtc, <br><br>Did you lose experience when you died? If so, it was an NPC. If not, it was an actor. <br><br>In any case, I'm not at all familiar with this incident and I'll look into it tomorrow. I imagine that there is more story to what was going on than you may have been privy to at your particular point of interaction. <br><br>There are many different types of dynamic events that take place in game. Not all of them have to do with killing, though that does play a role of one kind or another in many of them. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post:If the GM had picked up the pieces]</i></font> <br><br>The important thing to remember is that an NPC being played by a human is not a GM. They are an NPC in the world, and just happen to have a human brain behind them. They act in the world as an NPC and react to stimuli based upon a script and character profile. <br><br>Knowing how these things work, I'd say that there was probably something more to what was going on. If you see something of this nature in the future you might try to talk to the NPC to see what they are there for.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008284.html"><b>Smithing and Tinkering</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Why is blacksmithing getting revamped BEFORE tinkering?????]</i></font> <br><br>Blacksmithing is a skill that can be used by everyone. Tinkering is a skill that can only be used by gnomes. It makes more sense to work on blacksmithy first. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: STICK TO YOUR PROMISES. You said tinkering was next, now own up to your words.]</i></font> <br><br>I do not believe that I said this. I do recall saying that several of the tradeskills are being revamped, but did not put them in any specific order. Please be patient. Everyone wants to see their issue addressed next. We'll get to all that we have planned as we are able.</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
