<a name="newsitem967601914,82598,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Rowyl Infobits</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 7:18 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Sheesh, how many infobit posts can we do today? :)  Here's the latest round of quotes and excerpts from EverQuest's UI designer Rowyl:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008621.html"><b>Suggestions</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post:  1. If you have a wheel-mouse, how about enabling the wheel so that it can be used to scroll the text window? It would need to be pretty speedy, so I would suggest scrolling by page, not by line. <br><br>2. When healing yourself, would it be possible to stop your health bar shooting up and then settling back down to a lower value? <br><br>3. Could there be an 'exchange and bank' button on the bank screen that automatically transfers all your money to your bank vault and changes it into the highest value coin, so avoiding the rather laborious multiple-clicking. I would not consider this to be anti-roleplay because it is what you would ask a bank cashier to do anyway. <br><br>4. It would be really really good if there was an option to switch off the ability to right-click on a player to examine them. It is useful and fast to right-click to con MOBs, and when a player is in the way it is both annoying and time consuming, especially in a battle situation. <br><br>5. Pretty low priority, but it would be nice if containers remembered where they opened on screen. I would imagine the simplest solution to implement would be to store a location for each inventory slot, rather than for each container. If a container is in a particular inventory slot, that container uses the slots stored position when it opens. If another container is switched into that same slot, then it would use the same location. Locations would be updated when a container is moved around the screen.]</i></font><br><br>I will look into 1, 2, 4, and 5, I doubt number 3 is going to happen.<br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007814.html"><b>Ctrl-# Casting</b></a><br>I still plan to get ctrl-# = cast spell in, but I have other things to deal with first. Hopefully soon.<br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007771.html"><b>Guild List for Guild Leaders</b></a><br>The problem here is that the server doesn't keep a list of who's in a guild. <br><br>We have a list of guilds, and each character record has an index into that list. <br><br>With thousands of character per server it's not feasable to search the entire database to generate a list of who's in the guild. <br><br>While I agree this would be a nice feature, it's just not gonna happen. Sorry.<br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007769.html"><b>/Pause?</b></a><br>If I were to add a /pause # or /delay # command you would likely not be able to do anything during the pause (kinda like it is when you cast a spell). <br><br>It that ok?<br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007705.html"><b>Rowyl's Mission</b></a><br>I'm assigned to work on the user interface, I do NOT work on class related issues, or NPC AI, or pathing, or spells (except maybe the graphics for the UI elements), or skill, or items. <br><br>The main reason you see my changes now, is that they are small and relatively easy to do. The second reason being that most of my issue do not relate to class balance, or gameplay, and those changes are not made lightly. They have to be discussed and planned out. <br><br>So, you will continue to see UI changes while not seeing other issues changed. I'm sorry, but that is the way it's going to be.</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
