<a name="newsitem967601148,56469,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">GM Event on Quellious</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 7:05 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Soulsender was kind enough to write and send us the following report:<BLOCKQUOTE>GM Event last night in Quellious, Kurn's Tower<br> <br>    For some weeks now, an alliance of Iksar Swiftails and Greenmist Knights have been conducting a siege of Kurn's Tower in the Field of Bone. Fighting under the name "Architects of Kurn", the collective swore to rid the ruins from ceiling to basement of all that oppose Iksar traditions and defile the name of Kurn. Last eve this siege passed into the eyes of the Gods and a grand battle was staged.<br> <br>    In deepest night, numerous Bone Golems appeared in the Field of Bone menacing and threatening revenge for recent assaults on the tower. Swearing allegiance to one "Sleak Pox", the Bone Golems tore in to ranks of unseasoned Iksar hunting the field, before being dispatched by more veteran warriors. It was soon determined that the Golems were calling Kurn's home their own, and the tower was stormed once again.<br> <br>    Upon entrance, a brave Greenmist Knight was dispatched -hidden from the vision of dutiful dead- to discover the whereabouts of Sleak Pox. Not long thereafter, horrific cries rang out in the tower -the Knight had been set-upon by Shades and Lesser Spectres in the Dining Room of Kurn! Flying to his aid, the Architects of Kurn stormed the first staircase and ascended the bridge. A pitched battle was waged on the second landing before entrance to the hall was gained. <br> <br>    Unfortunately, at this time, hot Iksar blood seemed to overheat. Instead of our planned, cunning assault, single warriors charged in to the dining room to confront Pox on his own terms. I tell you, friends, it was near a slaughter! Although only two Iksar fell, the rest were forced to flee back the way they had come, to tend to wounds and plan anew.<br> <br>    During the plan and associated rescue of the dead, a great war of words was waged between the Chief Architects and Sleak Pox. Eventually, so riled did he become that, forgetting the safety of his undead legions, Sleak Pox decided to confront the gathering alone atop the tower bridge beyond the stairs. <br> <br>    The second battle was glorious to behold. The Touch of Hate did serve Cazic-Thule well, as Greenmist Knights delivered blow after blow on Sleak Pox. The swiftness of Iksar Monk attacks left him dazed, battered and broken. Try as he might, Sleak Pox was here no match for Iksar blades and fists bent on vengeance. He fell in a tumbling heap down the stairs and was pronounced dead!<br> <br>    Deep rejoicing -the likes of which, I think, has not graced the tower since Kurn's departure- did then occur. To follow up the great battle, the remaining Architects decided to launch an attack in to the basement, and fought deep in to the night for celebration.<br> <br>    Soulsender, Architect of Kurn<br>    Shadow Knight of the 17 Wound.<br> <br>    /ooc Everyone who attended this even had a fantastic time! It was a lower-level event, and so not attended by a ton of gawkers or     super-twinks. Most everyone taunted and stayed in character the whole time, and even the ninja-looting of Pox's loot did                 not serve to effect the evening badly.</BLOCKQUOTE>Thank you!
</SPAN><P><br>
<a name="newsitem967601038,71483,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">Aradune Infobits</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 7:03 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Verant Vice President Brad McQuaid made a few posts recently on the Gameplay Board:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009130.html"><b>Leveling in Kunark</b></a><br>I just leveled my mid 20s ranger in Lake of Ill Omen pretty quickly. <br><br>Velious, btw, is targetted for 35-60, but yes, Kunark is for all levels.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/006032-3.html"><b>Clipping Plane</b></a><br>Here's the deal: <br><br>The bug with the rain is very low priority. <br><br>Slightly higher priority is having a game designer go through ALL outdoor zones and revisit the max clipping distance associated with the zone. <br><br>IF the zone doesn't have an artifically limited clip for effect (eg. Toxxulia Forest), the game designer will make the max clip the farthest it can be based on the max distance used when exporting the zone (it can't go farther, else things will cease to draw correctly). <br><br>As stated before, several months ago when I posted on the subject, this is low priority (getting FA style quests in the game, revamping lesser used dungeons, working on Velious, etc. are all higher priority). <br><br>Other than the wierd rain bug and the fact that apparently several zones could indeed have their max clip increased, I do NOT believe there is any 'bug'.<br>--<br>Darkmatter, I know this is your personal crusade, and I respect that :)<br><br>We DID, in my opinion, get to the bottom of it: for some reason, either in code or in data, many of the zones' max clipping planes were apparently reduced at some point. <br><br>I think your problem is with the priority we are assigning this issue, and I apologize that it's not high enough for some of you. <br><br>The plan is to have a game designer go into the data for each zone and move the clipping plane maximum out as appropriate. <br><br>If that fails, we'll look at it in code (which would involve a programmer). But my inclination is that the data change will solve the problem. <br><br>Again, it's not very high on the priority list. The FA style quests are (and are near being ready for testing, btw.), as are the dungeon revamps (which will be focussed on after the FA style quests).<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009182.html"><b>Firiona Vie & "PlayElf"</b></a><br>Firiona Vie in PlayElf? <br><br>Bah, they couldn't pay her enough :)<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009182.html"><b>Artwork Getting More Risque in EQ?</b></a><br>I'll look at the art again, but I'm pretty sure she's wearing essentially the same costume. <br><br>I'm pretty sure Keith Parkinson is adding more fur and other minor modifications to her costume to reflect that it's rather cold in Velious (or at least, in most of it). <br><br>That said, her overall look will remain the same. <br><br>Mr_disco: we hope to have some introductory GM events near Velious launch that will explain her escape from the Iksar and the re-discovery of Velious. <br><br>Aegris: I'm pretty sure you can see a mock-up box cover on EB's web page -- it uses some initial Parkinson artwork.</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
<a name="newsitem967600695,60500,"></a> <SPAN CLASS="newstitle">More Gordon Infobits</SPAN>
<br>
 
<SPAN CLASS="newsreporter">- <a href="mailto:aurum@vaultnetwork.com" class="newsreporter"><b>Aurum</b></a> @ 6:58 PM PDT </SPAN>
<br>

<SPAN CLASS="newstext">
Gordon made quite a few more posts since the first infobit news report was made.  Here's all the latest from the Gameplay Board:<UL><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009142.html"><b>Clarity Duration Decrased?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Please look into wether or not the duration to clarity was decreased.]</i></font> <br><br>We haven't changed it. Rest assured that if it had been lessened, there would have been an explosion here on the boards.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009197.html"><b>Popup Ads on Official Boards</b></a><br>Erm. Sorry. I'll forward the info to our ad integration department. <br>--<br>Just realized that I wasn't clear in my last post, the intrusive ads will be taken down.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009206.html"><b>Tradesfolk Forum</b></a><br>Due to popular opinion, we've reopened the Coalition of Tradesfolk forum for the discussion of Tradeskills. <br><br>As an added bonus, the game designer who is now responsible for them will be on the board regularly. Enjoy!<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009136.html"><b>Quote that Broke the Camel's Back</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Yes, if you're soling, there's a boatload of downtime. If you have a well balanced group, you can fight with very little downtime for as long as you like.  Downtime is a problem if you are not in a well-balanced group. If you are soloing, then the price you pay for that is extended downtime.]</i></font> <br><br>Thanks for mentioning that Slackjaw and a_cleric00, it's very true. A well balanced group can maintain a very good pace. Frankly, if someone is ever medding 10 minutes out of every 12, they might want to look into trying to balance out their group with complementary classes. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Abashi gave a technical reason to avoid a philosophical one.  Quite simply, they don't want to change the pace of the game. ]</i></font><br><br>You are indeed correct on all counts except about avoiding the philosophical one :)  We've been saying for a long time that we are not going to make any drastic changes to the core foundations of EverQuest. If we did so, the game would no longer be "EverQuest". It would be bad business to make drastic foundational changes to a successful product. If you read the FAQ, there's an excellent section that explains doing just this.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009130.html"><b>Luck and Kunark</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Ok.. I'm not an idiot. I TRIED to get into Kunark. I guess I must just have the WORST luck on the planet. =( ]</i></font><br><br>Your luck cannot be worse than mine. Back in early beta, friends started referring to my character as "the Often Dead". It still follows me today :)<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009133.html"><b>Will you buy another Verant game?</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Right now i'd have to say yes, I'd buy another V game. I haven't agreed with some of their design and balancing decisions, but overall I enjoy the game and would certaintly try one of their future products. <br><br>One of my biggest gripes about Verant is their poor quality control. Broken quests, stuff in patches that didn't go live, stuff that went live that wasn't in the patch. Stuff that was in the patch but didn't work. I think they're getting better though and their next game will probably be better managed. Nothing like learning on the job]</i></font> <br><br>Thanks for the honest evaluation. It's far more useful when people bring up both positive and negative issues rather than being all on one side or the other all of the time. <br><br>Concerning some of the problems that you've cited, guilty as charged. We have indeed made some mistakes and will probably continue to make them from time to time. The goal of course is to learn from our mistakes and reduce the recurrence of the same mistakes.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009115.html"><b>/Yell Upgrades</b></a><br>I do think that it's a good idea, and it's been forwarded to Rowyl with the other good UI enhancements that have been recommended. However, as it is part of a wish list, it's not something that I can give a periodic status update about.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008968.html"><b>"The Lost Zones"</b></a><br>This text will be in the next version of the FAQ: <br><br>If you&#8217;ve ever read fantasy novels, you might have noticed that many if not most of them have a map of the world within the first few pages. These maps contain areas, cities, features, and sometimes, entire continents, that aren&#8217;t necessarily visited during the scope of the novel. They are there because they are part of the world, even if the protagonists never reach those locations. <br><br>EverQuest is no different in this respect. Sometimes, the areas listed on the maps name areas in existing zones. Other times, the listed areas are room for expansion later in the story. All the areas on the map that do not have a zone or area associated with them for possible future expansion. <br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009053.html"><b>Linkdeath</b></a><br>I appreciate the time that you took to write this up. Let me see if I can explain the current technology is as much detail. <br><br>Pets can only exist in the world when their owner also exists in the world, meaning that once the owner disappears, so does the pet. At the same time, the character goes linkdead, that character cannot reenter the game until they are removed from the world. <br><br>Once a character is removed from the world, the world has no knowledge of the existence of the character. As such, the world no longer processes data relative to the characater, since the character does not exist. That is why NORENT objects are removed as the character is being removed, since the world has no knowledge of the character once they are gone. <br><br>Certain parts of the description above are core system mechanics for EverQuest that it wouldn't make sense to change after several years of getting them operating just right. That said, we do have some plans to improve the current situation in the works. I can't comment specifically on them until we have some new things implemented and tested on the Test Server.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008261.html"><b>Target Variables</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: is there string you can insert into text that will insert your targets name into emotes and such? <br>monsters can get my name. /poke, /bonk, etc use the name of the target.. there has to be a way.. is it availiable to the users?]</i></font> <br><br>Roy and I have spoken about this and it is on his plate. We're also looking into allowing people to customize their own emote text while using canned animations. For instance, instead of /wave always returning "User waves at Bob", perhaps you could type "/wave waves happily at %T", which would return "User waves happily at Bob" (assuming Bob is the target). <br><br>No promises just yet on whether this will absolutely be implemented nor a specific timeframe. I'll look into seeing if I can get more information narrowed down in the near future.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008673.html"><b>Harvest Casting Time</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: The spell gives back aprox half a bubble of mana, not a FULL bubble by any means... ]</i></font><br><br>That would depend on what gear you are wearing. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: Why does Harvest have such a loonngg casting time?<br>Other mana regen type spells have a low casting time. Why? B ]</i></font><br><br>Those other spells do not instantly give a huge chunk of mana. The casting time, stun, and recast time associated with the spell account for that fact.<br><br><br><LI><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008804.html"><b>Pet Command Issues</b></a><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: If the above is not posible or you feel it is in some way unbalanceing I would like to ask if you can check the range on the "/pet report health" comand and posibly expand it. I realize you did this a few patches back but it seems to have grown smaller and this poses some seiour gamplay problems for me and other pet classes.]</i></font> <br><br>All pet commands work based on range to the pet. There is range associated with these commands both due to realism and to have some disadvantages associated with pets in certain cases. <br><br><font color=#072876><i>[Quote from original post: I would like to propose a third health bar to be blaced under the stamina bar that shows the pet's health. It could be green (you haven't used that color yet). I can't see how this would be unbalanceing.]</i></font> <br><br>Hitting F1 twice will target your pet. If you do this you can then hit /assist to target the creature again. We wouldn't really want to make the data more accessible than it currently is. The lack of immediatly and always-available data is one of the disadvantages mentioned above.</UL>
</SPAN><P><br>
